1425
00:00:45,840 --> 00:00:48,070
<font color=#FFFF00>In the time of the Messiah,</font>

1426
00:00:48,680 --> 00:00:52,992
<font color=#FFFF00>the Roman Empire grows
to span thousands of miles.</font>

1427
00:00:53,840 --> 00:00:56,673
<font color=#FFFF00>It is an empire nourished by blood</font>

1428
00:00:56,800 --> 00:00:58,916
<font color=#FFFF00>and secured by fear.</font>

1429
00:00:59,440 --> 00:01:01,112
<font color=#FFFF00>They will take everything you have.</font>

1430
00:01:02,360 --> 00:01:05,636
<font color=#FFFF00>They will invite you
to their games to watch others suffer</font>

1431
00:01:05,720 --> 00:01:07,119
<font color=#FFFF00>and forget what you have lost.</font>

1432
00:01:09,520 --> 00:01:12,796
<font color=#FFFF00>They will leave you with
nothing but bitterness...</font>

1433
00:01:14,960 --> 00:01:17,030
<font color=#FFFF00>...and desire for revenge.</font>

1434
00:01:17,320 --> 00:01:19,231
<font color=#FFFF00>You should have stayed away.</font>

1435
00:01:20,680 --> 00:01:22,716
<font color=#FFFF00>You should have killed me.</font>

1436
00:01:24,360 --> 00:01:26,032
<font color=#FFFF00>I will.</font>

1437
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:40,709
<font color=#FFFF00>Don't burn out
your horse too soon.</font>

1438
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:42,711
<font color=#FFFF00>Three laps to go!</font>

1439
00:01:42,800 --> 00:01:44,438
<font color=#FFFF00>Try keeping up, Judah!</font>

1440
00:01:44,520 --> 00:01:45,873
<font color=#FFFF00>Don't embarrass yourself!</font>

1441
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:47,228
<font color=#FFFF00>Watch your back, brother!</font>

1442
00:01:47,320 --> 00:01:49,276
<font color=#FFFF00>You're a prince, not a warrior!</font>

1443
00:01:49,360 --> 00:01:52,193
<font color=#FFFF00>Prince Judah Ben-Hur, a Jew.</font>

1444
00:01:53,840 --> 00:01:57,549
<font color=#FFFF00>Messala Severus,
his adopted brother, a Roman.</font>

1445
00:01:59,200 --> 00:02:03,671
<font color=#FFFF00>They were as devoted to each
other as they were competitive.</font>

1446
00:02:08,040 --> 00:02:09,075
<font color=#FFFF00>You're a cheat!</font>

1447
00:02:09,160 --> 00:02:10,798
<font color=#FFFF00>Cheat? All is fair to you Romans!</font>

1448
00:02:10,880 --> 00:02:12,029
<font color=#FFFF00>Oh, that's low!</font>

1449
00:02:12,120 --> 00:02:13,872
<font color=#FFFF00>Judah's father passed away</font>

1450
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:16,116
<font color=#FFFF00>holding onto the hope
that the two brothers</font>

1451
00:02:16,240 --> 00:02:19,676
<font color=#FFFF00>could be an example of unity
in this divided land.</font>

1452
00:02:19,760 --> 00:02:20,760
<font color=#FFFF00>Cheat!</font>

1453
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:24,720
<font color=#FFFF00>One more lap to go!</font>

1454
00:02:55,560 --> 00:02:56,595
<font color=#FFFF00>Judah.</font>

1455
00:02:57,760 --> 00:02:59,239
<font color=#FFFF00>Judah!</font>

1456
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:03,800
<font color=#FFFF00>Judah!</font>

1457
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:09,273
<font color=#FFFF00>Help!</font>

1458
00:03:36,760 --> 00:03:39,274
<font color=#FFFF00>Mother?</font>

1459
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:41,669
<font color=#FFFF00>Judah's hurt! Someone help!</font>

1460
00:03:41,760 --> 00:03:42,760
<font color=#FFFF00>Mama!</font>

1461
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:45,638
<font color=#FFFF00>Nanny. Nanny, help.
Take him. Take him.</font>

1462
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:48,669
<font color=#FFFF00>- Careful, careful.
- What happened? Judah?</font>

1463
00:03:49,160 --> 00:03:50,354
<font color=#FFFF00>Judah!</font>

1464
00:03:50,840 --> 00:03:52,640
<font color=#FFFF00>- He's lost a lot of blood.
- Is he all right?</font>

1465
00:03:52,720 --> 00:03:54,336
<font color=#FFFF00>- What happened?
- There was a rock.</font>

1466
00:03:54,360 --> 00:03:55,952
<font color=#FFFF00>Mother?</font>

1467
00:03:56,040 --> 00:03:57,712
<font color=#FFFF00>Quick, fetch a doctor for your brother.</font>

1468
00:03:57,840 --> 00:03:59,796
<font color=#FFFF00>Tirzah! Run!</font>

1469
00:03:59,880 --> 00:04:01,120
<font color=#FFFF00>- Esther?
- Yes, Father?</font>

1470
00:04:01,200 --> 00:04:02,952
<font color=#FFFF00>Prepare the room for Master Judah.</font>

1471
00:04:03,040 --> 00:04:04,720
<font color=#FFFF00>- Get water.
- Hurry, Esther.</font>

1472
00:04:05,480 --> 00:04:06,993
<font color=#FFFF00>Careful, careful.</font>

1473
00:04:07,360 --> 00:04:08,873
<font color=#FFFF00>Get some water.</font>

1474
00:04:08,960 --> 00:04:09,960
<font color=#FFFF00>Up.</font>

1475
00:04:10,960 --> 00:04:13,428
<font color=#FFFF00>He's badly hurt. What have you done?</font>

1476
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:15,397
<font color=#FFFF00>I haven't done anything.
It was an accident.</font>

1477
00:04:15,480 --> 00:04:17,198
<font color=#FFFF00>Judah was thrown from his horse.</font>

1478
00:04:17,280 --> 00:04:19,874
<font color=#FFFF00>- We were riding and...
- Racing!</font>

1479
00:04:19,960 --> 00:04:20,960
<font color=#FFFF00>Mum...</font>

1480
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:23,633
<font color=#FFFF00>What should I do?</font>

1481
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:26,553
<font color=#FFFF00>You've done enough. Now pray.</font>

1482
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:29,279
<font color=#FFFF00>My son, will he live?</font>

1483
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:32,976
<font color=#FFFF00>- Minerva...
- He will recover.</font>

1484
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:34,736
<font color=#FFFF00>- The doctor reassured us.
- ...Mother Goddess,</font>

1485
00:04:34,760 --> 00:04:35,954
<font color=#FFFF00>restore him by the skin.</font>

1486
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:38,016
<font color=#FFFF00>But, Mother, he looks
like he's in so much pain.</font>

1487
00:04:38,040 --> 00:04:39,996
<font color=#FFFF00>Thank your Messala for that.</font>

1488
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:49,831
<font color=#FFFF00>Be strong, Master Judah.</font>

1489
00:05:53,680 --> 00:05:54,829
<font color=#FFFF00>Wait. Wait.</font>

1490
00:05:57,680 --> 00:06:00,513
<font color=#FFFF00>You are like an angel.</font>

1491
00:06:08,240 --> 00:06:09,434
<font color=#FFFF00>Tirzah.</font>

1492
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:15,119
<font color=#FFFF00>Go to bed.</font>

1493
00:06:19,440 --> 00:06:20,873
<font color=#FFFF00>Good night.</font>

1494
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:34,589
<font color=#FFFF00>We have different gods, Messala.</font>

1495
00:06:58,120 --> 00:06:59,633
<font color=#FFFF00>Did we have fun?</font>

1496
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:40,515
<font color=#FFFF00>- Esther, dance with me.
- I'm not allowed.</font>

1497
00:07:40,640 --> 00:07:42,995
<font color=#FFFF00>Well, we can give people
something to talk about.</font>

1498
00:07:43,080 --> 00:07:44,832
<font color=#FFFF00>We can cause a scandal. Come on.</font>

1499
00:07:56,840 --> 00:07:57,875
<font color=#FFFF00>Oh, let me help you.</font>

1500
00:07:57,960 --> 00:07:59,632
<font color=#FFFF00>I have it. It's not your place.</font>

1501
00:08:02,080 --> 00:08:04,150
<font color=#FFFF00>You know there's a whole
world beyond Jerusalem.</font>

1502
00:08:04,240 --> 00:08:07,152
<font color=#FFFF00>Greece, Persia, Egypt.</font>

1503
00:08:07,240 --> 00:08:08,400
<font color=#FFFF00>I just want to experience it.</font>

1504
00:08:08,480 --> 00:08:10,118
<font color=#FFFF00>I'm tired of reading about it,</font>

1505
00:08:10,200 --> 00:08:12,236
<font color=#FFFF00>hearing about it from travelers.</font>

1506
00:08:12,320 --> 00:08:14,436
<font color=#FFFF00>- Are you?
- Yes.</font>

1507
00:08:14,520 --> 00:08:17,114
<font color=#FFFF00>- But you make it sound so easy.
- It's not easy.</font>

1508
00:08:17,200 --> 00:08:19,634
<font color=#FFFF00>But that's life.</font>

1509
00:08:19,720 --> 00:08:20,835
<font color=#FFFF00>Tirzah.</font>

1510
00:08:21,680 --> 00:08:24,638
<font color=#FFFF00>Could you help me
to my bedroom, please?</font>

1511
00:08:58,240 --> 00:09:01,198
<font color=#FFFF00>You spend
too much idle time with Messala.</font>

1512
00:09:01,720 --> 00:09:04,837
<font color=#FFFF00>If I didn't,
you'd have nothing to complain about.</font>

1513
00:09:09,680 --> 00:09:12,513
<font color=#FFFF00>"Oh, have mercy on me, world!</font>

1514
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:16,195
<font color=#FFFF00>"Not one of my 359 gods
will smile upon me."</font>

1515
00:09:16,280 --> 00:09:18,350
<font color=#FFFF00>Don't mock.</font>

1516
00:09:18,440 --> 00:09:21,318
<font color=#FFFF00>What's wrong with you?
It's supposed to be a celebration.</font>

1517
00:09:21,400 --> 00:09:23,516
<font color=#FFFF00>It's a celebration of your faith, not mine.</font>

1518
00:09:23,600 --> 00:09:26,239
<font color=#FFFF00>Well, that's the virtue of wine.
It doesn't discriminate.</font>

1519
00:09:26,760 --> 00:09:28,016
<font color=#FFFF00>So what happened with you and Tirzah?</font>

1520
00:09:28,040 --> 00:09:30,031
<font color=#FFFF00>Your mother doesn't want us speaking.</font>

1521
00:09:30,120 --> 00:09:31,553
<font color=#FFFF00>And who cares what Mother wants?</font>

1522
00:09:31,640 --> 00:09:33,358
<font color=#FFFF00>Your mother cares.</font>

1523
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:34,509
<font color=#FFFF00>And?</font>

1524
00:09:35,880 --> 00:09:38,792
<font color=#FFFF00>- Listen, Judah, I...
- You have feelings for Tirzah.</font>

1525
00:09:38,880 --> 00:09:40,199
<font color=#FFFF00>Messala, admit it.</font>

1526
00:09:40,280 --> 00:09:41,918
<font color=#FFFF00>What am I supposed to do with them?</font>

1527
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:43,513
<font color=#FFFF00>You and your family are royalty.</font>

1528
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:45,556
<font color=#FFFF00>And what does that matter?</font>

1529
00:09:45,640 --> 00:09:47,056
<font color=#FFFF00>I'd rather she was paying attention to you</font>

1530
00:09:47,080 --> 00:09:48,559
<font color=#FFFF00>than some other brute.</font>

1531
00:09:48,640 --> 00:09:49,675
<font color=#FFFF00>Thanks.</font>

1532
00:09:49,760 --> 00:09:51,656
<font color=#FFFF00>I'm not saying you're a brute,
I'm saying you're brutish.</font>

1533
00:09:51,680 --> 00:09:52,749
<font color=#FFFF00>Oh...</font>

1534
00:09:52,840 --> 00:09:55,593
<font color=#FFFF00>Simonides, go to bed. Messala!</font>

1535
00:09:56,320 --> 00:09:58,515
<font color=#FFFF00>- You and Tirzah would be like...
- Like what?</font>

1536
00:09:58,600 --> 00:10:02,309
<font color=#FFFF00>Like we were family.
We're not family, are we?</font>

1537
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:03,874
<font color=#FFFF00>Are we?</font>

1538
00:10:03,960 --> 00:10:06,633
<font color=#FFFF00>I'm just a lowly orphan
your family took in.</font>

1539
00:10:06,720 --> 00:10:08,631
<font color=#FFFF00>Oh, my God. Of course we're family!</font>

1540
00:10:08,720 --> 00:10:10,995
<font color=#FFFF00>You're my brother.
You'll always be my brother.</font>

1541
00:10:11,080 --> 00:10:12,911
<font color=#FFFF00>Everything I own is yours.</font>

1542
00:10:13,160 --> 00:10:14,832
<font color=#FFFF00>No. I'll never have your name.</font>

1543
00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:16,296
<font color=#FFFF00>And every time my name is spoken,</font>

1544
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:19,039
<font color=#FFFF00>it will be spoken alongside
stories of my grandfather.</font>

1545
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:20,439
<font color=#FFFF00>Until I earn it back.</font>

1546
00:10:22,640 --> 00:10:25,438
<font color=#FFFF00>Messala, wait. Wait!</font>

1547
00:10:27,760 --> 00:10:29,079
<font color=#FFFF00>Messala.</font>

1548
00:10:30,160 --> 00:10:31,840
<font color=#FFFF00>- Where are you going?
- I'm going to Rome.</font>

1549
00:10:32,520 --> 00:10:34,280
<font color=#FFFF00>Wait. What do you mean,
you're going to Rome?</font>

1550
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:35,435
<font color=#FFFF00>Messala, stop.</font>

1551
00:10:35,520 --> 00:10:38,796
<font color=#FFFF00>The Emperor's called for men to put
down the rebellion in Germania.</font>

1552
00:10:39,480 --> 00:10:41,869
<font color=#FFFF00>He's called for idiots to fight and die.</font>

1553
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:45,069
<font color=#FFFF00>I can't believe this.</font>

1554
00:10:45,160 --> 00:10:46,456
<font color=#FFFF00>After everything we've done for you,</font>

1555
00:10:46,480 --> 00:10:48,480
<font color=#FFFF00>you still want to go and fight
for those murderers!</font>

1556
00:10:48,560 --> 00:10:49,993
<font color=#FFFF00>The pay's steady.</font>

1557
00:10:50,080 --> 00:10:51,308
<font color=#FFFF00>"The pay's steady"?</font>

1558
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:53,550
<font color=#FFFF00>So I can come back to Tirzah
with stature and wealth.</font>

1559
00:10:53,640 --> 00:10:54,993
<font color=#FFFF00>But wealth doesn't mean anything.</font>

1560
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:57,040
<font color=#FFFF00>- It never does if you're rich.
- Messala, please.</font>

1561
00:10:57,120 --> 00:10:58,189
<font color=#FFFF00>Look, tell Tirzah...</font>

1562
00:10:58,280 --> 00:10:59,976
<font color=#FFFF00>If you have something
to say to her, say it yourself.</font>

1563
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:02,036
<font color=#FFFF00>Otherwise you're just walking away.</font>

1564
00:11:16,920 --> 00:11:18,069
<font color=#FFFF00>Judah?</font>

1565
00:11:19,680 --> 00:11:21,033
<font color=#FFFF00>Where's Messala?</font>

1566
00:11:32,040 --> 00:11:33,473
<font color=#FFFF00>Messala,</font>

1567
00:11:33,560 --> 00:11:36,199
<font color=#FFFF00>I hope this letter finds
you well, if at all.</font>

1568
00:11:37,040 --> 00:11:39,679
<font color=#FFFF00>As with all the others
I've sent over the past three years,</font>

1569
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:41,836
<font color=#FFFF00>I expect no response.</font>

1570
00:11:44,760 --> 00:11:48,992
<font color=#FFFF00>I can only hope that it is by your choice
and not by the way of your demise.</font>

1571
00:11:49,080 --> 00:11:51,310
<font color=#FFFF00>I always prefer
not to see my food before I eat it.</font>

1572
00:11:51,400 --> 00:11:52,674
<font color=#FFFF00>That's probably the best idea.</font>

1573
00:11:52,760 --> 00:11:54,751
<font color=#FFFF00>You would hardly recognize
your Jerusalem now.</font>

1574
00:11:55,920 --> 00:11:57,056
<font color=#FFFF00>What? What are you looking at?</font>

1575
00:11:57,080 --> 00:11:58,149
<font color=#FFFF00>The circus.</font>

1576
00:11:58,240 --> 00:11:59,736
<font color=#FFFF00>The Romans continue
to leave their mark</font>

1577
00:11:59,760 --> 00:12:01,637
<font color=#FFFF00>and build their circus.</font>

1578
00:12:01,720 --> 00:12:04,473
<font color=#FFFF00>When you come home,
I will honor the monstrosity</font>

1579
00:12:04,560 --> 00:12:07,358
<font color=#FFFF00>by humiliating you in one of those
chariots you Romans so love.</font>

1580
00:12:07,440 --> 00:12:08,440
<font color=#FFFF00>Yes, of course.</font>

1581
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:11,994
<font color=#FFFF00>But, brother, I do have news to tell you.</font>

1582
00:12:12,080 --> 00:12:13,115
<font color=#FFFF00>Here, try it.</font>

1583
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,349
<font color=#FFFF00>Two months ago,</font>

1584
00:12:14,440 --> 00:12:17,352
<font color=#FFFF00>Esther's father found
a wealthy Roman for her to marry.</font>

1585
00:12:17,440 --> 00:12:19,317
<font color=#FFFF00>- Hmm.
- Hmm.</font>

1586
00:12:19,400 --> 00:12:21,120
<font color=#FFFF00>We still have to find you
something special.</font>

1587
00:12:21,160 --> 00:12:22,776
<font color=#FFFF00>Oh, no, that's okay. I don't want anything.</font>

1588
00:12:22,800 --> 00:12:25,473
<font color=#FFFF00>I gave my blessing knowing
in my heart it was a mistake.</font>

1589
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:29,040
<font color=#FFFF00>I was reminded of how
I used to jest to Mother</font>

1590
00:12:29,080 --> 00:12:30,200
<font color=#FFFF00>that one day we would wed...</font>

1591
00:12:30,280 --> 00:12:31,793
<font color=#FFFF00>Go with God.</font>

1592
00:12:32,520 --> 00:12:34,351
<font color=#FFFF00>...knowing the thought
of her son, a prince,</font>

1593
00:12:34,480 --> 00:12:37,233
<font color=#FFFF00>marrying a servant
would send her to an early grave.</font>

1594
00:12:39,920 --> 00:12:41,319
<font color=#FFFF00>I couldn't let her go.</font>

1595
00:12:55,480 --> 00:12:57,471
<font color=#FFFF00>If you leave me,
you leave me with nothing.</font>

1596
00:13:01,320 --> 00:13:03,470
<font color=#FFFF00>She is now my wife, brother.</font>

1597
00:13:06,080 --> 00:13:07,877
<font color=#FFFF00>Despite the wonderful life
we have together,</font>

1598
00:13:07,960 --> 00:13:10,315
<font color=#FFFF00>Rome has come to lay
a hard hand on the city.</font>

1599
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:13,119
<font color=#FFFF00>Repeated attacks have left
them with little patience.</font>

1600
00:13:13,880 --> 00:13:17,236
<font color=#FFFF00>Thankfully,
we've been able to retain their favor.</font>

1601
00:13:17,320 --> 00:13:18,673
<font color=#FFFF00>Well, for now.</font>

1602
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:21,239
<font color=#FFFF00>Hear my plea.</font>

1603
00:13:21,560 --> 00:13:24,233
<font color=#FFFF00>Be safe. Return home.</font>

1604
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:26,550
<font color=#FFFF00>I will listen to stories of your travels.</font>

1605
00:13:26,640 --> 00:13:27,675
<font color=#FFFF00>Judah.</font>

1606
00:13:28,040 --> 00:13:30,000
<font color=#FFFF00>- What have you found?
- I don't know what it is.</font>

1607
00:13:30,120 --> 00:13:32,270
<font color=#FFFF00>I know what this is!
This is a Senet board.</font>

1608
00:13:32,360 --> 00:13:33,760
<font color=#FFFF00>- How much for this?
- Five shekels.</font>

1609
00:13:33,840 --> 00:13:37,594
<font color=#FFFF00>A Zealot,
and that he will be subject today</font>

1610
00:13:37,680 --> 00:13:42,071
<font color=#FFFF00>to the customary punishment
of crucifixion.</font>

1611
00:13:42,160 --> 00:13:44,276
<font color=#FFFF00>- No!
- May his punishment</font>

1612
00:13:44,360 --> 00:13:47,397
<font color=#FFFF00>stand as a warning.</font>

1613
00:13:51,880 --> 00:13:55,111
<font color=#FFFF00>- Ah, the Zealots.
- All they want is freedom.</font>

1614
00:13:55,200 --> 00:13:56,474
<font color=#FFFF00>And at what cost?</font>

1615
00:13:56,560 --> 00:13:57,629
<font color=#FFFF00>If they had their way,</font>

1616
00:13:57,720 --> 00:13:58,816
<font color=#FFFF00>they'll bring the whole
of Rome down on us.</font>

1617
00:13:58,840 --> 00:13:59,856
<font color=#FFFF00>Then where will our freedom be?</font>

1618
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:01,536
<font color=#FFFF00>- How much is it? Five?
- Thank you, My Lord.</font>

1619
00:14:01,560 --> 00:14:03,551
<font color=#FFFF00>There's freedom elsewhere.</font>

1620
00:14:04,720 --> 00:14:05,869
<font color=#FFFF00>Excuse me?</font>

1621
00:14:06,280 --> 00:14:07,759
<font color=#FFFF00>Love your enemies.</font>

1622
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:11,231
<font color=#FFFF00>"Love your enemies."
Well, that's very progressive.</font>

1623
00:14:11,720 --> 00:14:13,233
<font color=#FFFF00>It's the truth.</font>

1624
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:18,556
<font color=#FFFF00>God is love.
He made us to share that love.</font>

1625
00:14:19,920 --> 00:14:21,536
<font color=#FFFF00>And where will your love be
when the Romans</font>

1626
00:14:21,560 --> 00:14:23,232
<font color=#FFFF00>turn their anger on the rest of us?</font>

1627
00:14:23,440 --> 00:14:25,271
<font color=#FFFF00>Hate and fear are lies.</font>

1628
00:14:25,760 --> 00:14:27,040
<font color=#FFFF00>They turn us against each other.</font>

1629
00:14:28,240 --> 00:14:30,993
<font color=#FFFF00>Those are the lies that make us slaves.</font>

1630
00:14:31,080 --> 00:14:33,230
<font color=#FFFF00>He has a path planned for you.</font>

1631
00:14:33,320 --> 00:14:34,719
<font color=#FFFF00>If He has a path planned for me,</font>

1632
00:14:34,800 --> 00:14:36,392
<font color=#FFFF00>how am I better off than a slave?</font>

1633
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:40,918
<font color=#FFFF00>Why don't you ask her?</font>

1634
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:54,228
<font color=#FFFF00>Esther.</font>

1635
00:14:57,920 --> 00:14:59,717
<font color=#FFFF00>There's truth to what he's saying.</font>

1636
00:14:59,800 --> 00:15:01,199
<font color=#FFFF00>There must be something better.</font>

1637
00:15:02,080 --> 00:15:03,672
<font color=#FFFF00>Better than what?</font>

1638
00:15:04,120 --> 00:15:05,155
<font color=#FFFF00>Look around you.</font>

1639
00:15:05,240 --> 00:15:06,376
<font color=#FFFF00>The roads are lined
with the sick and poor.</font>

1640
00:15:06,400 --> 00:15:07,736
<font color=#FFFF00>We should be grateful
we're not one of them.</font>

1641
00:15:07,760 --> 00:15:09,936
<font color=#FFFF00>- Can you spare something, please?
- We can be more than grateful.</font>

1642
00:15:09,960 --> 00:15:13,475
<font color=#FFFF00>Esther, I'm not denying
the fact that the world is a cruel place.</font>

1643
00:15:13,600 --> 00:15:15,376
<font color=#FFFF00>But it's our responsibility
to take care of ourselves</font>

1644
00:15:15,400 --> 00:15:16,719
<font color=#FFFF00>and the ones we love.</font>

1645
00:15:17,640 --> 00:15:20,473
<font color=#FFFF00>If people took care
of themselves, we'd all be saved.</font>

1646
00:15:20,600 --> 00:15:23,433
<font color=#FFFF00>If God is righteous,
then we should do righteous things.</font>

1647
00:15:23,520 --> 00:15:26,353
<font color=#FFFF00>If there is a God, then why
doesn't He do right by the world?</font>

1648
00:15:45,320 --> 00:15:46,912
<font color=#FFFF00>Come. Follow me.</font>

1649
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:50,878
<font color=#FFFF00>Follow me.
Follow me. This way.</font>

1650
00:15:51,640 --> 00:15:53,551
<font color=#FFFF00>Let's go. Stay with me.</font>

1651
00:16:24,720 --> 00:16:26,073
<font color=#FFFF00>Who's there?</font>

1652
00:16:26,560 --> 00:16:30,599
<font color=#FFFF00>Jacob, stop. He's my brother.</font>

1653
00:16:30,680 --> 00:16:32,398
<font color=#FFFF00>Put the knife down.</font>

1654
00:16:34,360 --> 00:16:35,873
<font color=#FFFF00>Put it down.</font>

1655
00:16:42,480 --> 00:16:44,198
<font color=#FFFF00>Judah.</font>

1656
00:16:57,040 --> 00:16:59,315
<font color=#FFFF00>- What happened to him?
- He's wounded.</font>

1657
00:16:59,400 --> 00:17:01,960
<font color=#FFFF00>- Yes, I can see that. How?
- The cemetery.</font>

1658
00:17:02,080 --> 00:17:04,992
<font color=#FFFF00>Romans take the stones of our ancestors</font>

1659
00:17:05,080 --> 00:17:06,308
<font color=#FFFF00>to build their circus.</font>

1660
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:08,470
<font color=#FFFF00>Not anymore.</font>

1661
00:17:08,560 --> 00:17:11,120
<font color=#FFFF00>- You're Zealots!
- We fight for your freedom.</font>

1662
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:13,080
<font color=#FFFF00>From what I can see,
you get young boys injured.</font>

1663
00:17:13,760 --> 00:17:14,760
<font color=#FFFF00>We need a doctor.</font>

1664
00:17:14,880 --> 00:17:16,836
<font color=#FFFF00>No, a doctor would
inform the centurions.</font>

1665
00:17:16,920 --> 00:17:18,672
<font color=#FFFF00>Go and get a candle. Go.</font>

1666
00:17:24,560 --> 00:17:26,039
<font color=#FFFF00>I need your knife.</font>

1667
00:17:32,720 --> 00:17:34,039
<font color=#FFFF00>What's your name?</font>

1668
00:17:34,920 --> 00:17:37,036
<font color=#FFFF00>- Dismas.
- Dismas.</font>

1669
00:17:40,960 --> 00:17:43,428
<font color=#FFFF00>I hope you're proud of yourselves.</font>

1670
00:17:43,920 --> 00:17:45,638
<font color=#FFFF00>You know our aim.</font>

1671
00:17:45,720 --> 00:17:49,030
<font color=#FFFF00>Independence from Caesar,
ending the occupation of the Holy Land.</font>

1672
00:17:49,120 --> 00:17:51,350
<font color=#FFFF00>- By killing Romans?
- We settle scores.</font>

1673
00:17:51,440 --> 00:17:53,431
<font color=#FFFF00>Not here. Not in Jerusalem.</font>

1674
00:17:53,520 --> 00:17:57,479
<font color=#FFFF00>Dismas, it's a little bit
of pain and then it's done.</font>

1675
00:17:57,800 --> 00:17:59,119
<font color=#FFFF00>Let me see.</font>

1676
00:18:07,760 --> 00:18:09,079
<font color=#FFFF00>You're a part of this?</font>

1677
00:18:09,520 --> 00:18:11,192
<font color=#FFFF00>The man you love is a Roman!</font>

1678
00:18:11,280 --> 00:18:12,508
<font color=#FFFF00>We don't kill all Romans.</font>

1679
00:18:12,600 --> 00:18:14,670
<font color=#FFFF00>Well, that's not very
comforting to the dead ones.</font>

1680
00:18:15,520 --> 00:18:17,397
<font color=#FFFF00>If your father was alive,
he would support us.</font>

1681
00:18:17,480 --> 00:18:19,516
<font color=#FFFF00>You, I don't know,
so you can shut your mouth.</font>

1682
00:18:19,600 --> 00:18:22,194
<font color=#FFFF00>This is your home,
this is your land, too.</font>

1683
00:18:22,280 --> 00:18:23,838
<font color=#FFFF00>They turn our brothers into slaves</font>

1684
00:18:23,920 --> 00:18:25,512
<font color=#FFFF00>and that doesn't move you?</font>

1685
00:18:25,600 --> 00:18:27,192
<font color=#FFFF00>Killing doesn't get us up from under.</font>

1686
00:18:27,280 --> 00:18:29,714
<font color=#FFFF00>- Being passive has done what?
- It keeps the peace.</font>

1687
00:18:29,800 --> 00:18:31,199
<font color=#FFFF00>You confuse peace with freedom.</font>

1688
00:18:31,320 --> 00:18:32,594
<font color=#FFFF00>Jacob.</font>

1689
00:18:32,680 --> 00:18:36,070
<font color=#FFFF00>The High Priests,
you in the privileged class...</font>

1690
00:18:36,160 --> 00:18:38,993
<font color=#FFFF00>You get Caesar's favor
in exchange for obedience.</font>

1691
00:18:40,520 --> 00:18:42,192
<font color=#FFFF00>The rest of us get scraps.</font>

1692
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:49,513
<font color=#FFFF00>I won't condone violence.</font>

1693
00:18:51,520 --> 00:18:52,999
<font color=#FFFF00>Nobody's asking your permission.</font>

1694
00:18:57,560 --> 00:19:01,792
<font color=#FFFF00>You keep my family
and my house clean of this.</font>

1695
00:19:10,200 --> 00:19:11,599
<font color=#FFFF00>Now get out.</font>

1696
00:19:12,680 --> 00:19:15,240
<font color=#FFFF00>- The boy?
- He's safe here.</font>

1697
00:19:15,320 --> 00:19:16,639
<font color=#FFFF00>Safer than with you.</font>

1698
00:19:19,160 --> 00:19:20,832
<font color=#FFFF00>I said get out!</font>

1699
00:19:24,440 --> 00:19:26,556
<font color=#FFFF00>You know, Mother has
hopes for a grandchild.</font>

1700
00:19:26,640 --> 00:19:28,631
<font color=#FFFF00>She asks me every day. I tell her, "Soon."</font>

1701
00:19:30,120 --> 00:19:32,998
<font color=#FFFF00>But I know "soon"
isn't soon enough for her.</font>

1702
00:19:37,640 --> 00:19:39,119
<font color=#FFFF00>That sounds wonderful.</font>

1703
00:19:48,440 --> 00:19:49,440
<font color=#FFFF00>Judah Ben-Hur?</font>

1704
00:19:49,840 --> 00:19:51,193
<font color=#FFFF00>- Yes?
- Follow us.</font>

1705
00:19:51,280 --> 00:19:52,536
<font color=#FFFF00>Where are you taking him?</font>

1706
00:19:52,560 --> 00:19:54,080
<font color=#FFFF00>Don't worry, we've done nothing wrong.</font>

1707
00:19:54,120 --> 00:19:55,917
<font color=#FFFF00>It's all right, go inside.</font>

1708
00:20:16,200 --> 00:20:17,713
<font color=#FFFF00>I've brought the Jew.</font>

1709
00:20:29,840 --> 00:20:31,910
<font color=#FFFF00>I haven't changed that much, have I?</font>

1710
00:20:33,160 --> 00:20:34,752
<font color=#FFFF00>You look like one of those statues</font>

1711
00:20:34,840 --> 00:20:36,990
<font color=#FFFF00>you Romans insist on
putting everywhere.</font>

1712
00:20:37,480 --> 00:20:39,630
<font color=#FFFF00>You look like the clay
they make them from.</font>

1713
00:20:39,960 --> 00:20:41,757
<font color=#FFFF00>Statues are made of marble, not clay.</font>

1714
00:20:41,840 --> 00:20:43,353
<font color=#FFFF00>Not the one they'd make of you.</font>

1715
00:21:05,840 --> 00:21:07,353
<font color=#FFFF00>Look at this.</font>

1716
00:21:08,720 --> 00:21:09,789
<font color=#FFFF00>Wow.</font>

1717
00:21:11,480 --> 00:21:13,710
<font color=#FFFF00>Well, come on, tell me.
Tell me everything.</font>

1718
00:21:19,080 --> 00:21:20,308
<font color=#FFFF00>Up Mars!</font>

1719
00:21:26,880 --> 00:21:28,472
<font color=#FFFF00>Move forward!</font>

1720
00:21:28,840 --> 00:21:30,671
<font color=#FFFF00>Move forward!</font>

1721
00:21:31,600 --> 00:21:33,536
<font color=#FFFF00>I'm not sure
you want to hear everything.</font>

1722
00:21:33,560 --> 00:21:35,516
<font color=#FFFF00>And you were right
about life as a soldier.</font>

1723
00:21:37,640 --> 00:21:40,108
<font color=#FFFF00>Sleepless nights in the mud.
Cold and wet.</font>

1724
00:21:40,920 --> 00:21:42,592
<font color=#FFFF00>Drusus, move forward!</font>

1725
00:21:42,680 --> 00:21:45,069
<font color=#FFFF00>- If we stay here, we'll die!
- Then you go!</font>

1726
00:21:45,520 --> 00:21:46,748
<font color=#FFFF00>One night in Persia...</font>

1727
00:21:46,840 --> 00:21:47,909
<font color=#FFFF00>Your name?</font>

1728
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:49,274
<font color=#FFFF00>...I met him.</font>

1729
00:21:49,360 --> 00:21:52,955
<font color=#FFFF00>- Your name!
- Messala Severus.</font>

1730
00:21:53,080 --> 00:21:57,596
<font color=#FFFF00>Captain Messala Severus.
These are your men now.</font>

1731
00:21:58,440 --> 00:22:00,590
<font color=#FFFF00>- Start leading!
- Sir!</font>

1732
00:22:00,680 --> 00:22:02,910
<font color=#FFFF00>His name was Pontius Pilate.</font>

1733
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:04,592
<font color=#FFFF00>He gave me a chance.</font>

1734
00:22:04,680 --> 00:22:07,319
<font color=#FFFF00>He reminded me of
what we were fighting for.</font>

1735
00:22:07,400 --> 00:22:09,038
<font color=#FFFF00>Things you and I believe in, Judah.</font>

1736
00:22:09,720 --> 00:22:13,554
<font color=#FFFF00>A civilized world, progress,
prosperity, stability.</font>

1737
00:22:15,440 --> 00:22:17,271
<font color=#FFFF00>I battled and marched through countries</font>

1738
00:22:17,360 --> 00:22:20,477
<font color=#FFFF00>and across continents
I'd once dreamed of.</font>

1739
00:22:31,560 --> 00:22:34,870
<font color=#FFFF00>I led my men from battle to battle,
to the heights of glory.</font>

1740
00:22:36,480 --> 00:22:38,520
<font color=#FFFF00>But we crushed the freedom
of innocent civilizations</font>

1741
00:22:38,560 --> 00:22:40,790
<font color=#FFFF00>simply because they were different.</font>

1742
00:22:42,640 --> 00:22:44,631
<font color=#FFFF00>I saw much blood spilled.</font>

1743
00:22:47,560 --> 00:22:49,755
<font color=#FFFF00>More than I can describe.</font>

1744
00:22:50,920 --> 00:22:52,399
<font color=#FFFF00>Attention!</font>

1745
00:22:52,480 --> 00:22:54,994
<font color=#FFFF00>My true fight became
with my commander,</font>

1746
00:22:55,080 --> 00:22:56,399
<font color=#FFFF00>Marcus.</font>

1747
00:22:58,520 --> 00:23:00,158
<font color=#FFFF00>Why haven't you attacked the city?</font>

1748
00:23:00,240 --> 00:23:02,595
<font color=#FFFF00>An attack wasn't needed.
My orders were to pacify the city.</font>

1749
00:23:02,680 --> 00:23:04,477
<font color=#FFFF00>Leaving no able-bodied man alive.</font>

1750
00:23:04,600 --> 00:23:06,477
<font color=#FFFF00>Well, who will till the field or harvest...</font>

1751
00:23:06,600 --> 00:23:09,876
<font color=#FFFF00>We need to stamp out
revolt in every corner of the Empire.</font>

1752
00:23:09,960 --> 00:23:11,996
<font color=#FFFF00>If you want to offer up
another lifeless husk</font>

1753
00:23:12,080 --> 00:23:13,752
<font color=#FFFF00>- to the Empire...
- Messala Severus?</font>

1754
00:23:14,200 --> 00:23:16,919
<font color=#FFFF00>We've heard the stories
about your grandfather.</font>

1755
00:23:17,360 --> 00:23:19,271
<font color=#FFFF00>His hand in betraying Julius Caesar.</font>

1756
00:23:21,360 --> 00:23:23,590
<font color=#FFFF00>And how he wailed
when he was crucified.</font>

1757
00:23:24,760 --> 00:23:28,116
<font color=#FFFF00>In spite of that,
I'm thankful Pilate's on my side, brother.</font>

1758
00:23:28,640 --> 00:23:30,915
<font color=#FFFF00>More thankful to see you.</font>

1759
00:23:31,960 --> 00:23:33,188
<font color=#FFFF00>Me, too.</font>

1760
00:23:35,520 --> 00:23:37,520
<font color=#FFFF00>To think you were just
a lowly Hur before you left.</font>

1761
00:23:41,640 --> 00:23:43,000
<font color=#FFFF00>Well, Mother missed you every day.</font>

1762
00:23:43,600 --> 00:23:45,636
<font color=#FFFF00>Ah, I'm sorry I left you alone with her.</font>

1763
00:23:46,480 --> 00:23:47,629
<font color=#FFFF00>Tirzah?</font>

1764
00:23:48,120 --> 00:23:49,473
<font color=#FFFF00>How is she?</font>

1765
00:23:49,880 --> 00:23:51,711
<font color=#FFFF00>Tirzah's good, she's well.</font>

1766
00:23:53,880 --> 00:23:54,960
<font color=#FFFF00>Judah, will you tell her...</font>

1767
00:23:55,040 --> 00:23:57,120
<font color=#FFFF00>No, you can tell her yourself.
She's not yet married.</font>

1768
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:02,119
<font color=#FFFF00>My God, you still have it.</font>

1769
00:24:04,320 --> 00:24:05,639
<font color=#FFFF00>Why didn't you write?</font>

1770
00:24:06,680 --> 00:24:08,193
<font color=#FFFF00>What would I say?</font>

1771
00:24:09,920 --> 00:24:13,151
<font color=#FFFF00>I don't know.
That you're alive? That you're well?</font>

1772
00:24:13,760 --> 00:24:15,716
<font color=#FFFF00>Anything would have sufficed.</font>

1773
00:24:15,800 --> 00:24:17,153
<font color=#FFFF00>Judah,</font>

1774
00:24:17,280 --> 00:24:19,953
<font color=#FFFF00>I had to be able to come back
on my own terms.</font>

1775
00:24:20,520 --> 00:24:22,238
<font color=#FFFF00>Your family gave me everything.</font>

1776
00:24:23,040 --> 00:24:25,713
<font color=#FFFF00>I wanted to be able to return the favor.</font>

1777
00:24:25,800 --> 00:24:26,915
<font color=#FFFF00>Now I can.</font>

1778
00:24:30,080 --> 00:24:31,957
<font color=#FFFF00>Mmm. Judah, listen.</font>

1779
00:24:32,040 --> 00:24:33,520
<font color=#FFFF00>- I need your help.
- Messala.</font>

1780
00:24:42,160 --> 00:24:44,754
<font color=#FFFF00>You're needed outside.
There's been another attack.</font>

1781
00:24:48,840 --> 00:24:50,637
<font color=#FFFF00>Stretcher bearer, over here.</font>

1782
00:24:51,320 --> 00:24:53,436
<font color=#FFFF00>What's being said about Pontius Pilate?</font>

1783
00:24:53,520 --> 00:24:54,919
<font color=#FFFF00>To be honest, nothing good.</font>

1784
00:24:56,160 --> 00:24:58,016
<font color=#FFFF00>In a few days, he wants
to ride through Jerusalem</font>

1785
00:24:58,040 --> 00:24:59,473
<font color=#FFFF00>at the head of a legion.</font>

1786
00:24:59,720 --> 00:25:00,869
<font color=#FFFF00>Why?</font>

1787
00:25:01,720 --> 00:25:03,472
<font color=#FFFF00>The Zealots.</font>

1788
00:25:03,560 --> 00:25:06,518
<font color=#FFFF00>I've tried to deal with them peacefully.
Peace doesn't work.</font>

1789
00:25:07,040 --> 00:25:10,396
<font color=#FFFF00>- So now you try a legion.
- That's not my choice.</font>

1790
00:25:11,760 --> 00:25:13,751
<font color=#FFFF00>All they want from Rome
is their land back.</font>

1791
00:25:14,440 --> 00:25:17,318
<font color=#FFFF00>It was never their land.
It belonged to you, the wealthy.</font>

1792
00:25:17,400 --> 00:25:19,960
<font color=#FFFF00>You don't really believe
in a return to the Age of Solomon.</font>

1793
00:25:20,080 --> 00:25:22,216
<font color=#FFFF00>When the Zealots
are done with us, they'll turn on you.</font>

1794
00:25:22,240 --> 00:25:25,118
<font color=#FFFF00>I don't care about their politics.
I just care about keeping the peace.</font>

1795
00:25:25,200 --> 00:25:26,269
<font color=#FFFF00>Then we're agreed!</font>

1796
00:25:26,360 --> 00:25:28,635
<font color=#FFFF00>Look, Zealots are the common enemy.</font>

1797
00:25:28,720 --> 00:25:31,871
<font color=#FFFF00>Listen, you're a prince.
You have the ear of your people.</font>

1798
00:25:32,400 --> 00:25:34,994
<font color=#FFFF00>Pontius Pilate has to
ride through Jerusalem with no trouble.</font>

1799
00:25:35,080 --> 00:25:36,911
<font color=#FFFF00>That's all I'm asking.</font>

1800
00:25:38,200 --> 00:25:39,918
<font color=#FFFF00>Brother, I've been away a long time.</font>

1801
00:25:40,880 --> 00:25:44,190
<font color=#FFFF00>If I come back now,
believe me, it's important.</font>

1802
00:25:47,440 --> 00:25:48,919
<font color=#FFFF00>I want to give you this.</font>

1803
00:25:50,720 --> 00:25:52,631
<font color=#FFFF00>I've done a lot of work with this.</font>

1804
00:25:54,960 --> 00:25:56,473
<font color=#FFFF00>It would give me nothing but joy</font>

1805
00:25:56,560 --> 00:25:59,074
<font color=#FFFF00>to know it was in your hands
and lay forever idle.</font>

1806
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:10,789
<font color=#FFFF00>I'll speak to my people,
find out what I can.</font>

1807
00:26:10,920 --> 00:26:11,920
<font color=#FFFF00>Thank you.</font>

1808
00:26:12,240 --> 00:26:15,312
<font color=#FFFF00>- But you must come to dinner.
- I will.</font>

1809
00:26:15,400 --> 00:26:17,595
<font color=#FFFF00>But nothing special. Just a simple meal.</font>

1810
00:26:17,720 --> 00:26:19,711
<font color=#FFFF00>I promise. A simple meal.</font>

1811
00:26:22,920 --> 00:26:23,936
<font color=#FFFF00>What's this about?</font>

1812
00:26:23,960 --> 00:26:26,872
<font color=#FFFF00>There's been an attack
at the cemetery. Zealots.</font>

1813
00:26:26,960 --> 00:26:28,188
<font color=#FFFF00>Breathing still?</font>

1814
00:26:28,280 --> 00:26:30,430
<font color=#FFFF00>This is Vilarius. I know him.</font>

1815
00:26:30,520 --> 00:26:33,034
<font color=#FFFF00>Pull him out. Brother...</font>

1816
00:26:33,120 --> 00:26:35,680
<font color=#FFFF00>Lost quite a bit of blood.</font>

1817
00:26:36,800 --> 00:26:37,994
<font color=#FFFF00>Messala.</font>

1818
00:26:50,600 --> 00:26:52,192
<font color=#FFFF00>What happened, Lucius?</font>

1819
00:26:52,640 --> 00:26:53,993
<font color=#FFFF00>Zealots.</font>

1820
00:26:55,120 --> 00:26:57,475
<font color=#FFFF00>They poured through
the encampment under cover of night.</font>

1821
00:26:58,240 --> 00:27:00,231
<font color=#FFFF00>We had no way of...</font>

1822
00:27:00,320 --> 00:27:03,710
<font color=#FFFF00>The people's gratitude
for your bloodless suppression.</font>

1823
00:27:03,800 --> 00:27:05,199
<font color=#FFFF00>What were your men doing here?</font>

1824
00:27:06,160 --> 00:27:08,913
<font color=#FFFF00>Orders were to gather stones
to build the circus.</font>

1825
00:27:09,000 --> 00:27:10,672
<font color=#FFFF00>You understand this is sacred land.</font>

1826
00:27:10,800 --> 00:27:12,677
<font color=#FFFF00>These are Judean graves.</font>

1827
00:27:13,120 --> 00:27:15,111
<font color=#FFFF00>I'm informing Pilate.</font>

1828
00:27:15,680 --> 00:27:19,912
<font color=#FFFF00>If you rule as occupiers,
you will be met with disaster, I promise.</font>

1829
00:27:20,000 --> 00:27:22,958
<font color=#FFFF00>Are you as treasonous
as you are useless?</font>

1830
00:27:28,400 --> 00:27:29,958
<font color=#FFFF00>That's my brother's bow.</font>

1831
00:27:30,360 --> 00:27:31,679
<font color=#FFFF00>You should be resting.</font>

1832
00:27:35,080 --> 00:27:36,274
<font color=#FFFF00>I'm fine.</font>

1833
00:27:36,880 --> 00:27:38,791
<font color=#FFFF00>I need to redress the wound.</font>

1834
00:27:42,120 --> 00:27:43,189
<font color=#FFFF00>Sit.</font>

1835
00:27:48,680 --> 00:27:50,480
<font color=#FFFF00>Well, if you want to
call anywhere home again,</font>

1836
00:27:50,560 --> 00:27:51,879
<font color=#FFFF00>you'll need to be more careful.</font>

1837
00:27:52,120 --> 00:27:54,111
<font color=#FFFF00>The people you run with now are trouble.</font>

1838
00:27:55,520 --> 00:27:57,336
<font color=#FFFF00>I see they've sold you
on the romance of fighting,</font>

1839
00:27:57,360 --> 00:27:58,496
<font color=#FFFF00>but the reality is very different.</font>

1840
00:27:58,520 --> 00:27:59,999
<font color=#FFFF00>How would you know?</font>

1841
00:28:01,400 --> 00:28:04,198
<font color=#FFFF00>I know when I found you,
you were almost dead.</font>

1842
00:28:04,680 --> 00:28:06,352
<font color=#FFFF00>And for what?</font>

1843
00:28:06,440 --> 00:28:07,936
<font color=#FFFF00>So you can say
you evened up with the Romans?</font>

1844
00:28:07,960 --> 00:28:10,155
<font color=#FFFF00>We're not trying to balance anything.</font>

1845
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:12,520
<font color=#FFFF00>We want the freedom we were born with.</font>

1846
00:28:12,560 --> 00:28:15,056
<font color=#FFFF00>And if the Romans won't give it to us,
we'll have to take it by force.</font>

1847
00:28:15,080 --> 00:28:16,911
<font color=#FFFF00>How many Romans do you even know?</font>

1848
00:28:17,560 --> 00:28:20,677
<font color=#FFFF00>Have you ever had a conversation
with a single one in your life?</font>

1849
00:28:21,320 --> 00:28:23,601
<font color=#FFFF00>Don't spit your hate for all
when you don't even know one.</font>

1850
00:28:25,320 --> 00:28:27,595
<font color=#FFFF00>Now, you're welcome to stay
here as long as you need.</font>

1851
00:28:27,680 --> 00:28:29,576
<font color=#FFFF00>When you're well,
you should go back to your family.</font>

1852
00:28:29,600 --> 00:28:30,919
<font color=#FFFF00>I should.</font>

1853
00:28:31,520 --> 00:28:34,671
<font color=#FFFF00>But my father was able-bodied,
so the Romans killed him.</font>

1854
00:28:35,920 --> 00:28:39,435
<font color=#FFFF00>My mother was fertile,
so they did other things to her.</font>

1855
00:28:48,520 --> 00:28:50,033
<font color=#FFFF00>Everybody, just act normal.</font>

1856
00:28:53,680 --> 00:28:54,680
<font color=#FFFF00>He's coming.</font>

1857
00:28:54,920 --> 00:28:56,911
<font color=#FFFF00>Oh, for God's sake, more normal.</font>

1858
00:29:02,120 --> 00:29:03,439
<font color=#FFFF00>Welcome home.</font>

1859
00:29:04,920 --> 00:29:08,276
<font color=#FFFF00>This is Captain Drusus,
my second-in-command.</font>

1860
00:29:08,360 --> 00:29:10,191
<font color=#FFFF00>- Greetings.
- To you, Prince.</font>

1861
00:29:10,280 --> 00:29:11,679
<font color=#FFFF00>I owe this man my life.</font>

1862
00:29:11,760 --> 00:29:13,280
<font color=#FFFF00>We have something in common, at least.</font>

1863
00:29:22,640 --> 00:29:25,200
<font color=#FFFF00>I have a small gift from my travels.</font>

1864
00:29:29,280 --> 00:29:32,113
<font color=#FFFF00>The finest silk in all of Egypt.</font>

1865
00:29:33,080 --> 00:29:34,957
<font color=#FFFF00>It reminded me of you.</font>

1866
00:29:35,600 --> 00:29:38,353
<font color=#FFFF00>Your return is gift enough for me.</font>

1867
00:30:01,520 --> 00:30:02,999
<font color=#FFFF00>So</font>

1868
00:30:03,680 --> 00:30:05,796
<font color=#FFFF00>you never got married.</font>

1869
00:30:05,880 --> 00:30:08,553
<font color=#FFFF00>Don't they teach subtlety
in Caesar's army?</font>

1870
00:30:10,600 --> 00:30:12,591
<font color=#FFFF00>You must have a hundred men
fighting over you.</font>

1871
00:30:12,680 --> 00:30:13,829
<font color=#FFFF00>A few.</font>

1872
00:30:14,760 --> 00:30:16,512
<font color=#FFFF00>But you spoiled me for others.</font>

1873
00:30:16,600 --> 00:30:18,670
<font color=#FFFF00>- Oh, don't say that!
- It's true.</font>

1874
00:30:19,360 --> 00:30:22,272
<font color=#FFFF00>Well, you should be happy.
You deserve to be.</font>

1875
00:30:25,440 --> 00:30:28,432
<font color=#FFFF00>I know. I look like a monster.</font>

1876
00:30:29,360 --> 00:30:30,998
<font color=#FFFF00>Nothing like one.</font>

1877
00:30:31,640 --> 00:30:34,393
<font color=#FFFF00>You know this scar, of course.</font>

1878
00:30:34,520 --> 00:30:37,080
<font color=#FFFF00>- This one I got in Germania.
- Germania?</font>

1879
00:30:37,160 --> 00:30:38,957
<font color=#FFFF00>The other one I can't show you. I...</font>

1880
00:30:39,040 --> 00:30:40,760
<font color=#FFFF00>I was run through,
I thought fatally, and...</font>

1881
00:30:43,160 --> 00:30:44,878
<font color=#FFFF00>As I lay there, I...</font>

1882
00:30:45,960 --> 00:30:47,837
<font color=#FFFF00>I wished I could see you again.</font>

1883
00:30:47,920 --> 00:30:50,150
<font color=#FFFF00>Talk to you one last time.</font>

1884
00:30:54,120 --> 00:30:55,519
<font color=#FFFF00>Messala!</font>

1885
00:30:57,720 --> 00:30:59,233
<font color=#FFFF00>Let me show you something.</font>

1886
00:31:04,560 --> 00:31:06,869
<font color=#FFFF00>I may kill your brother one day.</font>

1887
00:31:07,440 --> 00:31:09,237
<font color=#FFFF00>I may kill him first.</font>

1888
00:31:10,560 --> 00:31:12,240
<font color=#FFFF00>You know, your mother
used to interrupt us.</font>

1889
00:31:12,280 --> 00:31:13,315
<font color=#FFFF00>Now you do.</font>

1890
00:31:13,400 --> 00:31:15,152
<font color=#FFFF00>- We have a lot to catch up on.
- Indeed.</font>

1891
00:31:15,880 --> 00:31:17,279
<font color=#FFFF00>It is striking.</font>

1892
00:31:17,360 --> 00:31:19,669
<font color=#FFFF00>Now tell me something
honestly. Look me in the eyes.</font>

1893
00:31:19,760 --> 00:31:22,120
<font color=#FFFF00>How many men does it take
to get you dressed in the morning?</font>

1894
00:31:24,280 --> 00:31:26,475
<font color=#FFFF00>- That's an honest question.
- Yeah.</font>

1895
00:31:26,560 --> 00:31:28,551
<font color=#FFFF00>Doesn't he look just like Zeus?</font>

1896
00:31:28,760 --> 00:31:30,955
<font color=#FFFF00>You know, he's twice as fast, though.</font>

1897
00:31:31,040 --> 00:31:32,758
<font color=#FFFF00>And I knew you'd appreciate him.</font>

1898
00:31:32,840 --> 00:31:34,592
<font color=#FFFF00>Cost me a small fortune.</font>

1899
00:31:37,720 --> 00:31:40,188
<font color=#FFFF00>He really is a beautiful horse.</font>

1900
00:31:40,280 --> 00:31:41,508
<font color=#FFFF00>Yes, he is.</font>

1901
00:31:41,600 --> 00:31:42,953
<font color=#FFFF00>So you spoke with your people.</font>

1902
00:31:43,080 --> 00:31:45,036
<font color=#FFFF00>Yes. I spoke to some of the local rabbis</font>

1903
00:31:45,120 --> 00:31:47,000
<font color=#FFFF00>and opinion makers,
and most of them want peace.</font>

1904
00:31:47,400 --> 00:31:48,753
<font color=#FFFF00>So who's against us?</font>

1905
00:31:49,560 --> 00:31:52,472
<font color=#FFFF00>Some local thugs and radicals.
No one of any importance.</font>

1906
00:31:52,560 --> 00:31:53,913
<font color=#FFFF00>Right, but who?</font>

1907
00:31:54,520 --> 00:31:56,078
<font color=#FFFF00>Messala, they don't matter.</font>

1908
00:31:56,160 --> 00:31:58,016
<font color=#FFFF00>But, Judah, if they don't matter,
then tell me who they are.</font>

1909
00:31:58,040 --> 00:31:59,155
<font color=#FFFF00>What are their names?</font>

1910
00:31:59,960 --> 00:32:01,757
<font color=#FFFF00>I'm not going to name names.</font>

1911
00:32:01,840 --> 00:32:03,040
<font color=#FFFF00>So you're going to stand idle,</font>

1912
00:32:03,120 --> 00:32:05,111
<font color=#FFFF00>even though you know who the guilty are.</font>

1913
00:32:05,920 --> 00:32:09,754
<font color=#FFFF00>To be honest, no one's guilty of anything
except being sick of Rome's oppression.</font>

1914
00:32:10,640 --> 00:32:12,915
<font color=#FFFF00>Are you aware who's riding to this city?</font>

1915
00:32:13,320 --> 00:32:15,038
<font color=#FFFF00>Did I make that clear?</font>

1916
00:32:15,160 --> 00:32:16,912
<font color=#FFFF00>Death or peace.</font>

1917
00:32:17,480 --> 00:32:19,198
<font color=#FFFF00>I've tried every other way.</font>

1918
00:32:19,280 --> 00:32:21,056
<font color=#FFFF00>And they spit my grandfather's
name in my face</font>

1919
00:32:21,080 --> 00:32:22,399
<font color=#FFFF00>- and ridicule me!
- Oh, my God.</font>

1920
00:32:22,480 --> 00:32:23,896
<font color=#FFFF00>After all these years, you still sound like</font>

1921
00:32:23,920 --> 00:32:25,956
<font color=#FFFF00>that Roman orphan who
turned up on our doorstep.</font>

1922
00:32:26,040 --> 00:32:28,190
<font color=#FFFF00>Judah, you promised to help me!</font>

1923
00:32:28,280 --> 00:32:30,840
<font color=#FFFF00>No, I said I would speak
to the people. And I have.</font>

1924
00:32:30,920 --> 00:32:33,753
<font color=#FFFF00>I don't need you to speak to them.
I need you to sway them.</font>

1925
00:32:33,840 --> 00:32:35,068
<font color=#FFFF00>And if you can't do that,</font>

1926
00:32:35,160 --> 00:32:37,071
<font color=#FFFF00>then I need you to tell me
who our enemies are.</font>

1927
00:32:37,160 --> 00:32:38,878
<font color=#FFFF00>Because we've run out of time.</font>

1928
00:32:39,560 --> 00:32:41,278
<font color=#FFFF00>Judah, please.</font>

1929
00:32:42,320 --> 00:32:45,676
<font color=#FFFF00>Please, I need you to help me.</font>

1930
00:32:47,000 --> 00:32:50,072
<font color=#FFFF00>Messala, I won't be bullied
into this decision.</font>

1931
00:32:54,520 --> 00:32:55,520
<font color=#FFFF00>Judah!</font>

1932
00:32:55,840 --> 00:32:58,149
<font color=#FFFF00>- Messala! Dinner!
- Oh...</font>

1933
00:32:58,920 --> 00:33:01,434
<font color=#FFFF00>Come on, let's get something to eat.</font>

1934
00:33:51,040 --> 00:33:53,235
<font color=#FFFF00>This is how Jerusalem welcomes us?</font>

1935
00:33:53,320 --> 00:33:56,357
<font color=#FFFF00>Tribune Messala has promised
there'll be no trouble.</font>

1936
00:33:56,720 --> 00:33:59,712
<font color=#FFFF00>I've spoken to prominent citizens.</font>

1937
00:34:00,120 --> 00:34:01,997
<font color=#FFFF00>Your safety is their highest priority.</font>

1938
00:34:11,560 --> 00:34:12,993
<font color=#FFFF00>What is that?</font>

1939
00:34:13,080 --> 00:34:14,479
<font color=#FFFF00>- Stay here.
- Why?</font>

1940
00:34:14,560 --> 00:34:15,754
<font color=#FFFF00>Please.</font>

1941
00:34:16,240 --> 00:34:17,389
<font color=#FFFF00>Tirzah?</font>

1942
00:34:17,480 --> 00:34:19,277
<font color=#FFFF00>Tirzah, wait for me.</font>

1943
00:35:14,320 --> 00:35:15,355
<font color=#FFFF00>No!</font>

1944
00:35:18,960 --> 00:35:19,960
<font color=#FFFF00>Sir!</font>

1945
00:35:20,160 --> 00:35:21,673
<font color=#FFFF00>Testudo!</font>

1946
00:35:22,440 --> 00:35:24,317
<font color=#FFFF00>- Testudo!
- Protect!</font>

1947
00:35:25,640 --> 00:35:26,789
<font color=#FFFF00>Shields up!</font>

1948
00:35:28,640 --> 00:35:29,993
<font color=#FFFF00>Ready arrows!</font>

1949
00:35:30,080 --> 00:35:31,080
<font color=#FFFF00>Judah!</font>

1950
00:35:31,600 --> 00:35:33,716
<font color=#FFFF00>Down! Mother, get Tirzah down!</font>

1951
00:35:34,840 --> 00:35:37,673
<font color=#FFFF00>Find the ones who did this and kill them!</font>

1952
00:35:38,480 --> 00:35:40,391
<font color=#FFFF00>You're responsible! Fix it!</font>

1953
00:35:41,680 --> 00:35:43,910
<font color=#FFFF00>Tirzah, move! Get inside. Inside!</font>

1954
00:35:44,200 --> 00:35:45,519
<font color=#FFFF00>Move!</font>

1955
00:35:46,800 --> 00:35:48,472
<font color=#FFFF00>Step aside!</font>

1956
00:35:48,840 --> 00:35:50,876
<font color=#FFFF00>Open this door!</font>

1957
00:35:51,000 --> 00:35:52,672
<font color=#FFFF00>Break down the door.</font>

1958
00:35:58,360 --> 00:36:00,157
<font color=#FFFF00>Open the door!</font>

1959
00:36:01,160 --> 00:36:03,469
<font color=#FFFF00>Open this door!</font>

1960
00:36:03,560 --> 00:36:04,959
<font color=#FFFF00>Dismas!</font>

1961
00:36:07,120 --> 00:36:08,269
<font color=#FFFF00>What have you done?</font>

1962
00:36:08,360 --> 00:36:10,715
<font color=#FFFF00>Do you realize what you've just done?</font>

1963
00:36:11,040 --> 00:36:12,536
<font color=#FFFF00>Then get ready
to down this door!</font>

1964
00:36:12,560 --> 00:36:14,278
<font color=#FFFF00>- Run!
- Take cover!</font>

1965
00:36:14,400 --> 00:36:16,152
<font color=#FFFF00>Go. Go!</font>

1966
00:36:18,040 --> 00:36:19,314
<font color=#FFFF00>We're friends of Rome.</font>

1967
00:36:19,400 --> 00:36:21,789
<font color=#FFFF00>This house is sovereign. This house...</font>

1968
00:36:21,880 --> 00:36:23,757
<font color=#FFFF00>Simonides!</font>

1969
00:36:23,840 --> 00:36:25,910
<font color=#FFFF00>On the ground
with all of them!</font>

1970
00:36:26,000 --> 00:36:28,150
<font color=#FFFF00>- Search every room.
- Mother!</font>

1971
00:36:28,240 --> 00:36:29,960
<font color=#FFFF00>Drag every one
of them in here, now!</font>

1972
00:36:30,040 --> 00:36:32,270
<font color=#FFFF00>I have to speak
to Messala Severus. He knows me!</font>

1973
00:36:32,360 --> 00:36:34,510
<font color=#FFFF00>If they resist, kill them.</font>

1974
00:36:34,600 --> 00:36:36,830
<font color=#FFFF00>- Come with me!
- Please, don't leave them!</font>

1975
00:36:36,920 --> 00:36:38,717
<font color=#FFFF00>- Tirzah!
- Get down here!</font>

1976
00:36:38,880 --> 00:36:40,791
<font color=#FFFF00>What are you doing?
Leave my daughter alone!</font>

1977
00:36:40,880 --> 00:36:43,678
<font color=#FFFF00>Wait, please! Please! No!</font>

1978
00:36:44,880 --> 00:36:46,074
<font color=#FFFF00>Please!</font>

1979
00:36:48,560 --> 00:36:49,834
<font color=#FFFF00>Listen to us!</font>

1980
00:36:49,920 --> 00:36:51,433
<font color=#FFFF00>I'll take all collaborators!</font>

1981
00:36:51,560 --> 00:36:52,560
<font color=#FFFF00>Judah!</font>

1982
00:36:52,640 --> 00:36:54,995
<font color=#FFFF00>Who shot the arrow?</font>

1983
00:36:56,320 --> 00:36:57,639
<font color=#FFFF00>Who shot the arrow?</font>

1984
00:36:59,400 --> 00:37:01,197
<font color=#FFFF00>Who shot...</font>

1985
00:37:08,720 --> 00:37:10,438
<font color=#FFFF00>No, wait! Please!</font>

1986
00:37:10,520 --> 00:37:11,589
<font color=#FFFF00>Wait!</font>

1987
00:37:28,520 --> 00:37:31,193
<font color=#FFFF00>Confess your crime!</font>

1988
00:37:31,280 --> 00:37:33,111
<font color=#FFFF00>We've done nothing.
We've done nothing!</font>

1989
00:37:33,200 --> 00:37:36,431
<font color=#FFFF00>Confess your crime,
or they all stand accused!</font>

1990
00:37:36,520 --> 00:37:37,794
<font color=#FFFF00>Accused of what?</font>

1991
00:37:39,280 --> 00:37:40,554
